  523|       |   * are masked out and that all of the high order bits of 'c' have been
  524|       |   * "moved" to 'a' (in the previous step).  This means that there are
  525|       |   * no overlapping bits in the addition -- so we can do a bitwise 'or'
  526|       |   * equivalently.
  527|       |   *
